Informatics and Statistics for Molecular Biologists (MOLB 7900) Course Overview

Informatics and Statistics for Molecular Biologists (MOLB 7900) Jay Hesselberth 2019-05-10 Course Overview Informatics and Statistics for Molecular Biologists (MOLB 7900) is offered at the University of Colorado School of Medicine and teaches students how to design and analyze common molecular biology experiments.
